<subsection xml:id="subsec-area-of-irregular-shapes">
    <title>Area of irregular shapes</title>
    <p>
        <m>\textbf{Recall:}</m>
    </p>
    <p>
        In the previous grades, you learnt about irregular shapes. What are some of the irregular shapes 
        did you come across.
    </p>
    <p>
        In this section, you will learn about area of irregular shapes you learn in grade <m>5</m> and 
        <m>7</m>
    </p>
    <definition xml:id="def-irregular-shapes">
        <statement>
            <p>
                <m>\textbf{Irreguar shapes}</m> are shapes that do not have 
                equal sides and angles.
            </p>
            <p>
                A kite,leaf,flowers and etc are some of the irregular shapes around.
            </p>
            <p>
                Look at the figure below for some irregular shapes around us.
            </p>
            <image source="/leaf.png" width="90%">
                <shortdescription>Irregular shapes</shortdescription>
            </image>
        </statement>
    </definition>
    <activity>
        <p>
        <m>\textbf{Work in groups}</m>
        </p>
        <p>
            <m>\textbf{Materials Needed:}</m>
        </p>
        <p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Graph paper with <m>1\,cm</m> squre grids.


                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        A pencil and ruler.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        An irregular shape (such as a kite).
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <p>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Work out the area of one square grid in the one centimetre squre grid.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                       <ol marker="(a)">
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                 On the square grid provided, draw a kite 
                                 covering several grid squares.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Count the fully covered squares inside the kite.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                       </ol>
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        <ol marker="(a)">
                            <li>
                                <p>
                                    Identify and estimate the partially 
                                    filled squares in the drawing.
                                </p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p>
                                    Divide the number of incomplete squares by two.
                                </p>
                            </li>
                        </ol>
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        <ol marker="(a)">
                            <li>
                                <p>
                                    Add the number of complete squares to half the number of incomplete 
                                    squares.
                                </p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p>
                                    Multiply the answer you got in step 4(a) by the area of the 
                                    square.
                                </p>
                            </li>
                        </ol>
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Discuss, compare and share your result with other groups in your class
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </activity>
    <p>
        <m>{\color{blue} \textbf{Essential Concept:}}</m>
    </p>
    <p>
        Drawing or tracing an irregular form on a square grid can allow you to estimate its area.  The area is approximated by counting the number of full unit squares and treating 
        incomplete squares as half squares.
    </p>
    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Estimate the area of the figure be low (<m>\textbf{in unit squares}</m>).
            </p>
            <image width="40%">
            <latex-image label="irregular1">
                \begin{tikzpicture}
                    % Draw the grid
                    \draw[black, thick] (-2.5,-2.5) rectangle (2.5,2.5);
                    \draw[black, dashed] (-2,-2.5) -- (-2,2.5);
                    \draw[black, dashed] (-1,-2.5) -- (-1,2.5);
                    \draw[black, dashed] (0,-2.5) -- (0,2.5);
                    \draw[black, dashed] (1,-2.5) -- (1,2.5);
                    \draw[black, dashed] (2,-2.5) -- (2,2.5);

                    \draw[black, dashed] (-2.5,-2) -- (2.5,-2);
                    \draw[black, dashed] (-2.5,-1) -- (2.5,-1);
                    \draw[black, dashed] (-2.5,0) -- (2.5,0);
                    \draw[black, dashed] (-2.5,1) -- (2.5,1);
                    \draw[black, dashed] (-2.5,2) -- (2.5,2);

                    % Draw the irregular shape
                    \draw[red, thick] plot[smooth cycle, tension=0.7] coordinates 
                    {(-1.8,-1.2) (-2,0) (-1.5,1.3) (-0.5,2) (0.8,1.8) 
                    (1.5,0.9) (1.2,-0.1) (0.8,-0.4) (0.4,-0.6) (-0.8,-1.5)};
                \end{tikzpicture}
            </latex-image>
               
            </image>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p>
                It is clearly showing that in the grid,
            </p>
            <p>
                The complete unit squress <m>= 3 </m>
            </p>
            <p>
                The incomplete unit squares <m>= \frac{10}{2}=5</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                Therefore,
            </p>
            <p>
                <md>
                    <mrow> A=\amp (3+5)\, \text{unit squares}</mrow>
                    <mrow> =\amp 7 \,\text{unit squares}</mrow>
                    
                </md>
            </p>
            <p>
                Therefore, the surface area of the ubove figure is <m>={\color{blue}  7 \,\textbf{unit squares} }</m>.
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>
    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Estimate the area of the shape below in square centimetres.
            </p>
            <image width="50%">
            <latex-image label="irregular2">
                \begin{tikzpicture}
                    % Draw the grid
                    \draw[very thick,step=1cm, purple] (-3,-3) grid (3,3);
                    
                    % Draw the adjusted leaf shape within the grid
                    \draw[very thick, blue] (-2,0) .. controls (-2,1) and (-1.5,2) .. (-1,2)
                    .. controls (-0.5,2.5) and (0.5,2.5) .. (1,2)
                    .. controls (1.5,2) and (2,1) .. (2,0)
                    .. controls (2,-1) and (1.5,-2) .. (1,-2)
                    .. controls (0.5,-2.5) and (-0.5,-2.5) .. (-1,-2)
                    .. controls (-1.5,-2) and (-2,-1) .. (-2,0);
                \end{tikzpicture}
            </latex-image>
                
            </image>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p>
                From the scetch below it clearly denot that,
            </p>
            <image width="50%">
            <latex-image label="Irregular3">
                \begin{tikzpicture}
                    % Draw the grid
                    \draw[very thick ,step=1cm, purple] (-3,-3) grid (3,3);
                    

                    
                    % Draw the adjusted leaf shape within the grid
                    \draw[very thick, blue] (-2,0) .. controls (-2,1) and (-1.5,2) .. (-1,2)
                    .. controls (-0.5,2.5) and (0.5,2.5) .. (1,2)
                    .. controls (1.5,2) and (2,1) .. (2,0)
                    .. controls (2,-1) and (1.5,-2) .. (1,-2)
                    .. controls (0.5,-2.5) and (-0.5,-2.5) .. (-1,-2)
                    .. controls (-1.5,-2) and (-2,-1) .. (-2,0);
                    
                    % Manually place numbers for fully enclosed squares 1 to 8
                    \node[black] at (-0.5,1.5) {\textbf{1}};
                    \node[black] at (0.5,1.5) {\textbf{2}};
                    \node[black] at (-0.5,0.5) {\textbf{3}};
                    \node[black] at (0.5,0.5) {\textbf{4}};
                    \node[black] at (-0.5,-0.5) {\textbf{5}};
                    \node[black] at (0.5,-0.5) {\textbf{6}};
                    \node[black] at (-0.5,-1.5) {\textbf{7}};
                    \node[black] at (0.5,-1.5) {\textbf{8}};
                    
                    
                    % The incompleted squres.
                    \node[blue] at (0.5,2.5) {\textbf{1}};
                    \node[blue] at (-0.5,2.5) {\textbf{2}};
                    \node[blue] at (-1.5,1.5) {\textbf{3}};
                    \node[blue] at (-1.5,0.5) {\textbf{4}};
                    \node[blue] at (-1.5,-0.5) {\textbf{5}};
                    \node[blue] at (-1.5,-1.5) {\textbf{6}};
                    \node[blue] at (-0.5,-2.5) {\textbf{7}};
                    \node[blue] at (0.5,-2.5) {\textbf{8}};
                    \node[blue] at (1.5,-1.5) {\textbf{9}};
                    \node[blue] at (1.5,-0.5) {\textbf{10}};
                    \node[blue] at (1.5,0.5) {\textbf{11}};
                    \node[blue] at (1.5,1.5) {\textbf{12}};
                \end{tikzpicture}
            </latex-image>
                
            </image>
            <p>
                The complete unit squress <m>= 8 </m>
            </p>
            <p>
                The incomplete unit squares <m>= \frac{12}{2}=6</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                Therefore,
            </p>
            <p>
                <md>
                    <mrow> A=\amp (8+6)\, \text{ square centimetres}</mrow>
                    <mrow> =\amp 14 \,\text{square centimetres}</mrow>
                    
                </md>
            </p>
            <p>
                Therefore, the Estimated area of the ubove shape  is <m>={\color{blue} 14 \,\text{square centimetres}}</m>.
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>
    <p>
        <m>\textbf{Follow-up activity:}</m>
    </p>
    <p>
        During your free time, trace your fingers on a square grid and calculate the area of 
        your finger. What is the area?
    </p>
    
    <p>
        <m>\textbf{Some digital activities for you.}</m>
    </p>

    
    

   



    




 



    
